# Agent implementation pattern
Each agent implements: assembleContext(input) -> callModel(ctx) -> validate(output) -> execute(actions).
- assembleContext is deterministic and pulls the relevant App Model subgraph + retrieved artifacts.
- callModel goes through the model gateway only; pinned model, temp 0, zod response schema, recorded to trajectory.
- validate parses the model output against a zod schema; reject on parse failure (no coercion of garbage).
- Tools are passed in via an allowlist; an agent cannot call a tool not in its allowlist.
- Deterministic heuristics run BEFORE the LLM and resolve as many cases as possible without it.
- The Self-Healer's output type cannot represent an assertion change (enforce via the type, see invariant 1).
